60 "§41-23-173
61 (a) The authority shall have the following duties:
62 (1) Encourage the education and training of aerospace
63 professionals to pioneer the frontier of space and to develop
64 new methods and technologies for the exploration of space.
65 (2) Promote new space exploration, space tourism, and
66 spaceport technologies across a wide spectrum of corporate,
67 academic, public, and private innovation infrastructures.
68 (3) Sponsor aerospace conferences and business
69 roundtables to enable networking among key aerospace leaders
70 and public officials.
71 (4) Encourage the leveraging of venture capital and
72 seed public-private partnerships to promote entrepreneurship
73 and expand space enterprise.
74 (5) Propose business initiatives, tax credits, small
75 business incubator programs, and other initiatives to
76 stimulate economic development and innovation within the
77 aerospace and space systems communities.
78 (6) Perform a study on the feasibility of securing
79 approval for the State of Alabama to have a federally licensed
80 spaceport.
81 (7) Encourage space research and education centers to
82 support these programs and facilitate technology transfer.
83 (8) Work with the Department of Tourism, the Alabama
84 U.S. Space Science Exhibit and Rocket Center Commission, and
Page 3

U.S. Space Science Exhibit and Rocket Center Commission, and
SB228 Enrolled
85 other public agencies to communicate the multiple scientific,
86 educational, and commercial benefits of space exploration and
87 the legacy of Alabama's contributions to America's space
88 program to the public and to promote space tourism and
89 training.
90 (9) Develop strategies to promote and encourage private
91 investments in furtherance of this article.
92 (10) Perform any other actions necessary or convenient
93 to carry out its purposes and to exercise its powers pursuant
94 to this article to the extent permitted by law.
95 (b) The authority shall establish procedures for
96 conducting its affairs in execution of the duties and
97 responsibilities stated in this article, which operating
98 procedures shall include appropriate operational guidelines.
99 The authority may establish committees to conduct the work of
100 the authority and the committees may include nonmembers as
101 deemed appropriate by the authority."
102 "§41-23-174
103 For the purpose of accomplishing the duties enumerated
104 in Section 41-23-173, the authority shall have the following
105 powers:
106 (1) To acquire by purchase or gift any real, personal,
107 or mixed property necessary or convenient in connection with
108 the purpose for which the authority is formed and to hold
109 title to such property, together with all rights incidental to
110 its estate in such property.
111 (2) To lease all or any part of the facilities or
112 property of the authority to any person and, from time to
Page 4

