113 time, fix, revise, charge, and collect rentals under such
114 leases.
115 (3) To adopt bylaws and policies, as approved by ADECA,
116 to administer this article, including any bylaws necessary to
117 meet the future needs of aerospace and spaceport
118 infrastructure and capabilities in this state. Upon the
119 adoption, amendment, or repeal of a bylaw or policy, the
120 authority shall provide a copy to the Legislative Council for
121 review.
122 (4) To make, enter into, and execute contracts,
123 agreements, leases, and other instruments with public and
124 private entities, and to take such other actions as may be
125 necessary or convenient to accomplish any purpose for which
126 the authority was organized or to exercise any power granted
127 under this article.
128 (5) To accept gifts, loans, and grants to expend in
129 taking any action not specifically prohibited by this article
130 in furtherance of the purposes of this article."
131 Section 2. This act shall become effective on October
132 1, 2026.
